10:
Even when the gods turn a blind
eye... My holy sword will right all
wrongs!
15:
A godly display. I guess I shouldn't
be surprised, with you being the
chosen one and all.
19:
C-cut it out, Nimbus! Stop teasing
me!
23:
It looks like you're getting a little
used to it now, though.
27:
N-no, not at all! Just the thought of
my friends and family seeing me like
this terrifies me!
40:
The Righteous Swordswoman...
That's you, Rinoa? Seriously?!
55:
I've been discovered by a friend... My
life is over...
64: Is it really that big of a deal?
68:
I-it's because... I can't go on living
after she saw me making such a
shameful display of myself...
73:
Right. So you're saying that what
you enjoy doing is a "shameful
display"?
77:
N-no, but... I just can't stand the
thought of someone I know seeing
me like that...
81:
There's that crap again... Just try
approaching them with something
like: "Here comes Rinoa, stylish
swordswoman at your service!"
86: I-I-I couldn't say something like that!
90:
No? Then maybe you should change
your name to "Rinoa, Scaredy-Cat
Swordswoman."
94:
Don't talk like that! I'm seriously
worried here!
107:
She's not ready for this yet. We can't
keep dragging her along if she's
gonna keep acting all worked up.
117:
He doesn't get it. I'm more capable
than he thinks—
121:
What the hell are you doing out
here?!
132:
Are you trying to ruin your father's
image, wandering around this filthy
downtown area?
134:
You drew this? I believe I told you to
leave that vulgar hobby behind!
136:
Shame on you! I believe I've already
taught you how to behave as
someone from our standing in
society!
142:
What is this, Rinoa? It's not proper for
a lady like yourself to fight!
144:
It was their fault! Bullying is wrong!
The kid they were after didn't do
anything bad!
146:
When that happens, get help. You're
a lady. You don't need to fight.
148:
That's right, Rinoa. We ladies have
our own way of doing things. I
taught you this, didn't I?
158:
Miss Rinoa of the Attic family... Why
are you here? Don't tell me you're
the one who dragged Layna into
this...
168: Where is it? M-my sword is missing?!
171:
I'm disappointed that a daughter
from a family like yours would act
like this. Your parents would be
miserable if they found out what
you're doing.
179:
N-no, you're wrong! My parents
have nothing to do with this!
184:
I came here of my own volition!
L-Layna, too!
187:
And I won't allow you to stomp on
her work like that! Even if you're her
father!
193:
Ahh, um... Layna! I'm sorry I surprised
you! You see, um, I'm actually...
196:
Ah... I can't believe it! My friend,
Rinoa... Was actually my favorite
adventurer this whole time?!
202:
I-I'm actually a big fan of
adventurers, just in secret. I've been
drawing fanart too, so... Um!
225:
I guess we can return the sword
later.
228:
We'll keep cheering you from the
sidelines, Rinoa... I mean, Righteous
Swordswoman!
232: Y-Yeah! I-I'll keep doing my best!
